[{"question":"What\u0027s wrong with that?","answer":"Well, the problem is several things.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":43,"aSentId":44},{"question":"And what is wrong with giving the poorer sections, the needier sections of society a bit of hope and even if for most of them it turns out in the end to be a hope that isn\u0027t realized?","answer":"Well, because it\u0027s false hope.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":57,"aSentId":58},{"question":"You\u0027ve got no way of knowing, have you?","answer":"Well, we actually do know it.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":102,"aSentId":103},{"question":"And I guarantee, most everybody realizes I probably won\u0027t win tonight, but what if?","answer":"I mean, you make it sound wonderfully harmless.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":114,"aSentId":115},{"question":"Now that is a huge chunk of change, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"It\u0027s -- government gambling has been a failed revenue source across the country, whether it\u0027s Massachusetts, California, you name it.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":128,"aSentId":129},{"question":"What is actually your problem with that?","answer":"But if you have sales -- that money comes from $4.7 billion worth of sales.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":136,"aSentId":137},{"question":"Which one should I do?","answer":"Well, I\u0027m going to sidebar for just a second on you and then come back to that if I can.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":185,"aSentId":186},{"question":"I mean, there\u0027s got to be somebody tomorrow possibly who\u0027ll be re-watching this avidly as I\u0027m sure they do every night, and saying, Dave Ramsey, I just won half a billion dollars, you know, what are you talking about?","answer":"And there\u0027s 175 million that\u0027ll be watching -- I hope your ratings were that good tomorrow night -- that didn\u0027t win.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":207,"aSentId":208},{"question":"Does America suffer when taxes are slightly higher in terms of its economic prosperity, or is that just a bit of a myth?","answer":"Well, I think there\u0027s a lot of theories out there running around and you know I\u0027ve got the formal education in finance degree and so I\u0027ve studied economics like a lot of folks have, and I was formally schooled in Keynesian economics.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":216,"aSentId":217},{"question":"Steven Rattner, is there a principle or is it just bloody minded news now by Republicans led by Grover Norquist, we shall not pay anymore taxes ever?","answer":"At some point, of course, there is such a thing as too much tax.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":272,"aSentId":273},{"question":"Putting your pragmatic hats on, if you were in that negotiating room, Emil Henry, what would the deal be?","answer":"Broadly speaking, here\u0027s where I think this has to end up.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":330,"aSentId":331},{"question":"Steven Rattner, if you were in that room and that was on the table what would you say?","answer":"I would say you need to have a compromise that\u0027s more in the middle.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":349,"aSentId":350},{"question":"Is this becoming a tax on the poor?","answer":"It is a tax on the poorer and the numbers bare that out.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":431,"aSentId":432},{"question":"I mean, it\u0027s a gimmick, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"It is a gimmick.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":451,"aSentId":452},{"question":"Were you surprised?","answer":"MILEY: Not at all.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":465,"aSentId":466},{"question":"What should they be thinking now?","answer":"Well, first of all, my preference, my preference is for the president to be more progressive.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":499,"aSentId":500},{"question":"And very quickly, what\u0027s the number one priority to try and eradicate poverty, would you say?","answer":"Jobs, jobs, jobs, and jobs with a living wage.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":531,"aSentId":532},{"question":"Do you appreciate that, too?","answer":"Well, I\u0027ve got to tell you honestly, Piers, I\u0027ve been doing this almost 23 years, and there has been nothing but goodness coming as far as I can see.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":565,"aSentId":566},{"question":"And Yolanda, are you allowed to play the lottery or not?","answer":"Nobody in the New York Lottery can play.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":575,"aSentId":576},{"question":"What is the biggest amount of money you\u0027ve won on a scratch card?","answer":"Oh, I think I won $250 in the state of Georgia.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":584,"aSentId":585},{"question":"You decided not to retire?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":587,"aSentId":588},{"question":"If you won -- obviously, I know you can\u0027t, I\u0027m talking metaphorically, if you won a half a billion dollars, as the Powerball now is tonight what would you spend it on?","answer":"I think right now -- I mean I\u0027ve always thought I\u0027d buy an exotic island or a bunch of cars for friends and family.","docId":"121128pmt","qSentId":592,"aSentId":593}]